(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFE7FFD8FF79FE64FF14FE7E" box="[159,233,438,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[256,1329,189,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-19@61.[247,1340,181,1929]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 8. Eudocima kinabaluenis and Eudocima homaena group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605514/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 8</figureCitation>
: C–D, 18: J, 30: J, 94: A–C)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE7FFD8FF71FE08FC04FDB7" blockId="15.[151,1436,402,537]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
The forewing differs from 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE7FFD8FE22FE09FDACFE5A" box="[452,593,474,500]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendida">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE7FFD8FE22FE09FDACFE5A" box="[452,593,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. splendida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that the green patch bulges distally at vein Cu2, the reniform is less distinct, and the outer wing margin is crenulate. All specimens are from Borneo.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
